The method can be formulated as follows:\
\\begin\{equation\}\
\\frac\{V^\{n+1\}_i - V^n_i\}\{\\Delta t\} = \\frac\{1\}\{2\} \\left( L^n V^n_i + L^\{n+1\} V^\{n+1\}_i \\right)\
\\end\{equation\}\
\
Here, $V^\{n+1\}_i$ is the option price at the next time step, $V^n_i$ is the option price at the current time step, $\\Delta t$ is the time step size, and $L$ is the differential operator reflecting the Black-Scholes PDE. The terms $L^n V^n_i$ and $L^\{n+1\} V^\{n+1\}_i$ represent the explicit and implicit parts of the method, respectively.\
