By using the weighting factor of $\\frac\{1\}\{2\}$, the Crank-Nicolson method effectively averages the explicit and implicit updates, providing a scheme that is both stable and accurate. This method is particularly well-suited for financial applications where the solution must be robust over a range of different market conditions and over time.\
